            'adhunik-momo-hub' => [
                'description' => '<p>Adhunik Mo:Mo Hub is a modern (adhunik means "modern" in Nepali) take on Nepal\'s most loved food — the momo dumpling — with a menu that extends far beyond the traditional steamed buffalo variety to include an ever-expanding repertoire of innovative fillings, cooking styles, and presentation formats.</p><p>Tandoori momos baked in a clay oven, momo burgers served in brioche buns, chocolate and cream cheese dessert momos, and deconstructed momo soup in individual portions are just some of the creative interpretations on offer. The original steamed and fried classics remain available for purists. A dedicated momo cooking class runs on Saturday mornings.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '10:00 AM – 9:30 PM (open daily)',
