            'pokhara-pizza-house' => [
                'description' => '<p>Pokhara Pizza House has been feeding pizza-hungry travellers since the early days of Pokhara\'s tourist boom, and its dedication to wood-fired, slow-fermented pizza dough has never wavered. The sourdough base — proved for a minimum of 48 hours — creates a crust with a complex, slightly tangy flavour and the perfect balance of crisp and chewy.</p><p>Toppings cover the classics (margherita, pepperoni, quattro formaggi) alongside inventive Nepali-inspired combinations: yak cheese and forest mushroom, buffalo mozzarella with local Himalayan herbs, and the popular "Annapurna" pizza with smoked chicken, caramelised onions, and house chilli oil. Available by the slice from 12 PM.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '11:00 AM – 10:30 PM (open daily) | By-the-slice from 12:00 PM',
                'features' => $this->features(['48-hour proved sourdough dough', 'Wood-fired oven', 'By-the-slice from noon', 'Yak cheese topping', 'Nepali herb combinations', 'Classic Italian and original options', 'Takeaway & delivery', 'Vegan cheese available', 'Free Wi-Fi', 'Group orders welcome']),
            ],
            'pokhara-thakali-kitchen' => [
                'description' => '<p>Pokhara Thakali Kitchen is the city\'s most revered destination for authentic Thakali cuisine — the distinctive culinary tradition of the Thakali people of the Kali Gandaki valley in Mustang district. Thakali food sits at the intersection of Tibetan and Nepali cooking, with a character all its own: deeply aromatic, richly spiced, and built for mountain altitudes.</p><p>The signature Thakali set meal is a revelation: a copper thali with buckwheat bread, yak butter rice, five or six revolving vegetable and meat dishes, thick lentil soup, and the house-made timur pickle that sparks the lips with Sichuan-like heat. The restaurant sources directly from Thakali farming families in Mustang and Baglung districts.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '10:30 AM – 9:30 PM (open daily)',
                'features' => $this->features(['Authentic Thakali cuisine', 'Copper thali service', 'Buckwheat bread specialty', 'Timur (Sichuan pepper) pickle', 'Direct Mustang sourcing', 'Yak butter dishes', 'Seasonal vegetable rotation', 'Vegetarian Thakali available', 'No artificial additives', 'Takeaway thali available']),
            ],
            'taal-restro-bar' => [
                'description' => '<p>Taal Restro & Bar (taal meaning "lake" in Nepali) is a vibrant lakeside venue that perfectly captures the festive energy of Pokhara\'s evening Lakeside scene. With a terrace directly overlooking Phewa Lake, a full bar, and a music policy that keeps the energy high without overpowering conversation, Taal has become a default evening venue for both first-timers and returning visitors.</p><p>The food menu covers all the popular categories: wood-fired pizza, pasta, burgers, Nepali plates, and a comprehensive momo section. The bar is particularly strong on local Nepal Ice craft beers and a cocktail list that makes creative use of locally distilled raksi spirits. DJ sets on Friday and Saturday evenings from 9 PM.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '11:00 AM – midnight (Fri & Sat until 1:00 AM)',
                'features' => $this->features(['Lakeside terrace', 'DJ sets Fri & Sat from 9 PM', 'Nepal Ice craft beers', 'Local raksi cocktails', 'Wood-fired pizza', 'Full momo menu', 'Live sport TV screens', 'Happy hour 5–8 PM', 'Group bookings', 'Free Wi-Fi']),
            ],
            'tree-house-restro' => [
                'description' => '<p>Tree House Restro is Pokhara\'s most whimsical dining destination — a restaurant built around and through a magnificent old banyan tree, with dining platforms at multiple levels connected by wooden walkways, rope bridges, and spiral staircases. Eating here, among the tree\'s sprawling branches, is an experience that delights adults and absolutely thrills children.</p><p>The menu is broad and approachable, spanning Nepali comfort food, Indian curries, continental classics, and a comprehensive children\'s menu. The higher platforms, accessible by the steeper staircases, offer treetop views of the surrounding neighbourhood and glimpses of the Annapurna range. Sunset drinks on the top deck are a particularly popular activity.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '8:00 AM – 10:00 PM (open daily)',
                'features' => $this->features(['Built into a live banyan tree', 'Multi-level treehouse platforms', 'Rope bridges & spiral staircases', 'Treetop mountain views', 'Children\'s menu', 'Family-friendly', 'Broad international menu', 'Sunset top-deck drinks', 'Free Wi-Fi', 'Group bookings']),
            ],
            'cafe-camellia-pokhara' => [
                'description' => '<p>Café Camellia is named after the camellia sinensis plant — the source of all true teas — and this devotion to the art of tea is the café\'s defining character. With a menu spanning over 60 varieties of Nepali, Indian, Chinese, Japanese, and blended teas, Café Camellia offers a tea education as well as a dining experience.</p><p>The food menu complements the tea philosophy with light, refined dishes: finger sandwiches, scones with clotted cream, tea-infused cakes, and afternoon tea sets that offer a Himalayan take on the English tradition. The café also hosts monthly tea tastings and serves as an outlet for selected Ilam and Annapurna region tea estates.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '8:00 AM – 8:00 PM (open daily) | Monthly tea tasting: first Saturday',
                'features' => $this->features(['60+ tea varieties', 'Nepali Ilam tea specialist', 'Afternoon tea sets', 'Scones & clotted cream', 'Tea-infused cakes', 'Monthly tea tasting events', 'Tea estate retail', 'No alcohol served', 'Quiet contemplative atmosphere', 'Free Wi-Fi']),
            ],
            'the-kebab-king' => [
                'description' => '<p>The Kebab King reigns supreme in Pokhara\'s street food scene — a counter-style restaurant that has elevated the art of the grilled kebab to royal heights. Open-air charcoal grills visible from the street produce the smoke signal that draws meat lovers from across Lakeside every evening.</p><p>The menu is focused and confident: seekh kebab, boti kebab, chicken tikka, reshmi kebab, and shami kebab, each marinated in house-ground spice blends and grilled to order over live charcoal. Wraps, rolls, and rice plates are available for a complete meal. The Kebab King sauce — a house-made chilli and herb condiment — has developed a cult following.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '12:00 PM – 10:30 PM (open daily)',
                'features' => $this->features(['Live charcoal grill visible', 'House-ground spice marinades', 'Seekh & boti kebabs', 'Chicken tikka specialty', 'Cult-status Kebab King sauce', 'Kebab wraps & rolls', 'Budget-friendly', 'Takeaway available', 'Counter dining', 'Catering available']),
            ],
            'caffe-concerto' => [
                'description' => '<p>Caffè Concerto brings the convivial spirit of an Italian café bar to the shores of Phewa Lake. The name evokes a musical gathering — and true to this, the café plays a carefully curated mix of Italian jazz, classical guitar, and acoustic pop that creates an atmosphere perfectly suited to lingering espressos, shared pasta, and relaxed conversation.</p><p>The espresso programme uses a house-blend of Italian and Nepali single-origin beans, roasted by a partner in Kathmandu and pulled through a La Marzocco machine — arguably the best espresso in Pokhara. The kitchen produces fresh pasta daily, with four sauces rotating on a weekly basis, accompanied by excellent antipasti and a concise Italian wine selection.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '8:00 AM – 10:30 PM (open daily)',
                'features' => $this->features(['Italian-Nepali coffee blend', 'La Marzocco espresso machine', 'Fresh pasta daily', 'Italian jazz atmosphere', 'Antipasti selection', 'Italian wine list', 'Aperitivo hour 6–8 PM', 'Tiramisu signature dessert', 'Free Wi-Fi', 'Outdoor lakeside tables']),
