            'momotarou-japanese-restaurant' => [
                'description' => '<p>Momotarou Japanese Restaurant is Pokhara\'s only dedicated Japanese dining destination — a genuine slice of Japan in the Himalayan foothills. Founded by a Japanese chef who relocated to Nepal after working in Tokyo and Kyoto restaurants, Momotarou brings authentic Japanese culinary discipline to a setting that provides its own extraordinary context.</p><p>The menu spans ramen (six broth styles), sushi and sashimi using Himalayan river fish and imported salmon, udon, gyoza, and a carefully selected Japanese whisky collection. The restaurant follows the Japanese ethos of shokunin — craftsman spirit — in every dish, from the precision of the sushi rice temperature to the clarity of the dashi broth.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '12:00 PM – 9:30 PM (closed Tuesdays)',
