            'vegan-way' => [
                'description' => '<p>Vegan Way is Pokhara\'s pioneering vegan restaurant — a bright, modern space that has been challenging the notion that Nepali cuisine cannot be fully vegan since its founding. The kitchen proves otherwise with a menu that demonstrates the astonishing richness and variety of plant-based Nepali and international cooking.</p><p>The fully vegan menu includes authentic Nepali dishes prepared without any animal products: vegan dal bhat with eight vegetable preparations, vegan momos filled with jackfruit and tofu, vegan sekuwa using marinated tempeh, and a celebrated vegan milk tea made with cashew milk and Ilam tea. The restaurant uses zero single-use plastic and composts all kitchen waste.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '8:00 AM – 9:30 PM (open daily)',
