            'med5-restaurant' => [
                'description' => '<p>Med5 Restaurant is named for the five signature spice blends that the chef developed over years of culinary training across South Asia and the Mediterranean. These five blends — Himalayan, Moroccan, Lebanese, Indian, and Greek — are the backbone of a menu that ranges widely but always maintains a coherent spice-forward identity.</p><p>The result is a menu that finds unexpected harmony: a Himalayan-spiced lamb chop with Moroccan couscous, a Lebanese-inspired mezze plate with Indian chutneys, and a Greek salad with Himalayan salt and local cheese. Med5 has developed a loyal following among Pokhara\'s food-forward community who appreciate its thoughtful, creative approach to global flavours.</p>',
                'opening_hours' => '11:30 AM – 10:30 PM (open daily)',
