            'san-chon-korean-restaurant' => [
                'description' => '<p>San Chon Korean Restaurant brings the communal, fire-at-the-table experience of Korean BBQ to Pokhara — the only restaurant in the valley to do so authentically. Each table is equipped with a built-in charcoal grill, and the parade of small dishes (banchan) that precede the main grill items is a meal in itself.</p><p>The menu covers the Korean BBQ essentials: samgyeopsal (thick-cut pork belly), bulgogi (marinated beef), dak-galbi (spicy chicken), and galbi (short ribs), alongside Korean classics like bibimbap, japchae, and the spicy kimchi jjigae stew. The house-made kimchi, fermented on-site, is exceptional.</p>',
