            'pokhara-sekuwa-house' => [
                'description' => '<p>Pokhara Sekuwa House is dedicated entirely to the art of sekuwa — the ancient Nepali tradition of marinating meat in spices and wood-fire roasting it over hardwood embers. The restaurant has perfected its technique over many years, and the result is sekuwa of such quality that the restaurant supplies several hotel restaurants in Pokhara.</p><p>The house marinade is a closely guarded recipe of over 20 spices and herbs, including jimbu, timur, and local wild oregano. Buffalo sekuwa, mutton sekuwa, chicken sekuwa, and the premium Himalayan yak sekuwa (available seasonally) are the main offerings. Everything is served with sautéed greens, beaten rice (chiura), and the house hot sauce.</p>',
